malaysian central bank see higher 1987 growth gross domest product ( gdp ) growth in 1987 is expect to grow by between 1.5 and two pct , up from one pct in 1986 , the central bank said . the forecast compar with the one pct gdp growth forecast made by the treasuri last octob . bank negara also said in it annual report that gross nation product ( gnp ) is expect to grow by 3.5 to four pct , after declin 7.3 pct in 1986. it said that a turnaround in investor confid sinc last novemb had been spur by a moder improv in oil and commod price and a rise in manufactur export . growth in 1987 is expect to come from the anticip rise in export earn if the industrialis countri sustain their averag gnp growth at 2.5 to three pct , it ad . bank negara said it forecast assum that crude oil will averag 15.50 dlr a barrel , rubber at 210 cent a kilo , palm oil at 850 ringgit a tonn , tin at 17 ringgit a kilo and a rise of 12 pct in manufactur export . it said malaysia 's intern term of trade will turn around to rise by two pct in 1987 after declin 12 pct in 1986 and five pct in 1985 . `` in 1987 , incom will be higher , privat consum spend is like to recov and expand ... the budget will remain under strict control ... the resourc gap in the govern 's financ on current account will be bridg over the near term , '' bank governor jaafar hussein said in the report . the current account deficit is expect to narrow to 1.19 billion ringgit in 1986 or 1.8 pct of gnp from 1.79 billion or 2.5 pct of the gnp the previou year . the bank forecast the inflat rate will increas by 1.5 pct , after it 0.7 pct rise in 1986 .